{
  "doc_id": "51136",
  "text": "It has been suggested that the increased secretion of urokinase (EC 3.4.21 . 3 1) observed in inflammatory bowel disease (Elliott et al. 1987; [CITATION_1] ) may lead to increased urokinase activity at intercellular junctions and result in increased intestinal permeability [CITATION_2] . Butyrate causes a concentration-dependent suppression of urokinase secretion by colonic crypt cells in vitro [CITATION_3] ) and therefore may be beneficial to patients with inflammatory bowel disease by improving intestinal barrier function.",
